  • Method Details

    • setUp

      @BeforeEach public void setUp()
      Called before each test is run.

    • tearDown

      @AfterEach public void tearDown()
      Called after each test has concluded

    • testDefaultConstructor

      @Test @DisplayName("Fish()") public void testDefaultConstructor()
      Tests the default constructor: Fish(). Does the following three times:
      1. Create a new Fish using the default constructor.
      2. Checks the value of age to ensure it is within the expected range (0 to 4).
      3. Checks the value of gender to ensure it is either MALE or FEMALE.

    • testConstructor

      @Test @DisplayName("Fish(int, Gender)") public void testConstructor()
      Tests the constructor: Fish(int, Gender). Does the following:
      1. Create a new Fish using the above constructor.
      2. Checks the value of age to ensure it is the value that it was set to.
      3. Checks the value of gender to ensure it is the value that it was set to.
      4. Create a new Fish using the above constructor, with an age that is out of bounds.
      5. Check the Fish's age, ensuring that is 9 (the Fish's maxAge)
      6. Check the Fish's gender, ensuring that it is the value it was set to.

    • testMaxAge

      @Test @DisplayName("maxAge()") public void testMaxAge()
      Tests the Fish.maxAge() method:
      1. Tests a Fish who's age is less than the max.
      2. Tests a Fish who's age is the max.

    • testGetAge

      @Test @DisplayName("getAge()") public void testGetAge()
      Tests the Animal.getAge() method. Does the following 5 times:
      1. Generates a random number between 0 and 9 (inclusive).
      2. Creates a new Fish with the randomly generated age.
      3. Ensures that the Fish#getAge() method returns the age generated.

    • testIncrAge

      @Test @DisplayName("incrAge()") public void testIncrAge()
      Tests the Fish.incrAge() method:
      1. Attempt to increment the age of a Fish who's age is less than 9 (the maximum age of a Fish).
      2. Attempt to increment the age of a Fish who's age is 9.

    • testRandomness

      @Test @DisplayName("Randomness Test") public void testRandomness()
      Tests the randomness of the random generation used to randomly generate a Fish's age and gender. Generates 100 random Fish objects. Then:
      1. Calculates the standard deviation and standard error of the ages of the Fish objects.
      2. Ensures that the mean age doesn't exceed +/- 2 * standard error (a 95% confidence interval).
      3. Calculates the percentages of the Fish objects' genders.

    • testToString

      @Test @DisplayName("toString()") public void testToString()
      Tests the Fish.toString() method. Does the following 5 times:
      1. Generates a random age and gender for the Fish.
      2. Creates the Fish object using the above two values.
      3. Ensures that the value returned by Fish.toString() contains each value that the Fish was instantiated with.
